    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[Er55b] Erd\\H{o}s, P., On amicable numbers. Publ. Math. Debrecen (1955), 108-111.\n \n [Gu04] Guy, Richard K., Unsolved problems in number theory. (2004), xviii+437.\n \n [Po15] Pomerance, Carl, On amicable numbers. (2015), 321-327.\n \n [Po81] Pomerance, Carl, On the distribution of amicable numbers. {II}. J. Reine Angew. Math. (1981), 183-188.",
      "remarks": "For example $220$ and $284$. Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er55b} proved that $A(x)=o(x)$, and Pomerance \\cite{Po81} improved this to\\[A(x) \\leq x \\exp(-(\\log x)^{1/3})\\]and later \\cite{Po15} to\\[A(x) \\leq x \\exp(-(\\tfrac{1}{2}+o(1))(\\log x\\log\\log x)^{1/2}).\\]This is problem B4 in Guy's collection \\cite{Gu04}."
    },
